list.abstract: produce（英 [prəˈdjuːs , ˈprɒdjuːs]，美 [prəˈduːs , ˈprɑːduːs]），英语单词，作动词时，为生产；制造；引起。作名词时，为产品；物产；成果。短语搭配有produce electricity（发电）。例句为“Structural inequities and discrimination produce health disparities .（结构性不平等和歧视会产生健康差异。）” produce动词类近义词有attract、cause等，名词类有manufacture、work等，不及物动词类有turn out、bring in。

yingyinNormal.en: This vast quantity of corn makes it possible to produce beef on an industrial scale.
yingyinNormal.zh: 巨量的玉米让这一切成为可能，让我们能够以工业级的规模生产牛肉。

yingyinNormal.en: We no longer see the beauty of life, but only what it can do for our species, what it enables us to produce.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们再也看不到美好的生命，我们只顾着利用地球，只顾着加快生产。

yingyinNormal.en: Banks then channel the savings into investment in new plants, skills and techniques that let us produce more.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这样银行就能把储蓄的钱转向投资于新工厂、发展新技术以及提高我们的生产效率。

yingyinNormal.en: Fear of foreign competition once led countries to try and produce everything they needed and impose heavy taxes to keep out foreign goods.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对外国竞争感到的恐惧让一些国家决定自给自足，自行生产所有产品，并且向国外的商品收相当重的税。

yingyinNormal.en: In the future, all the manufacturers, they make the machines, the machines can not only produce the products, the machines must talk, the machine must think.
yingyinNormal.zh: 未来的世界，所有的制造商制造什么机器，这些机器不仅会生产产品，它们必须说话，它们必须思考。

yingyinNormal.en: He pointed out that even if a country can produce pretty much everything at the lowest possible cost, with what economists call an absolute advantage, it's still better to focus on the products it can make most efficiently, that sacrifice the least amount of other goods, and let the rest of the world do the same.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他指出即使一个国家能用最低的成本生产所有东西，也就是经济学家所说的拥有「绝对利益」最好的还是专注于最有效率的生产并放弃其他选项，而让其他国家也做相同的事。

yingyinNormal.en: I told you. I told you in the produce aisle. I remember that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我告诉过你，在买菜的时候，我记得。

yingyinNormal.en: But these power plants produce more of our electricity than any other source.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是，大部分发电站还是使用同一种能源，也就是最常见的。

yingyinNormal.en: But her cows produce a lot of waste, and she's found a brand-new way to use it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但她的奶牛就浪费不少了，她找到了一个新方法加以利用。

yingyinNormal.en: Ugly grandchildren. But you're lovely. You're bound to produce little Imbeciles!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我担心的是生个丑孙子，但是你很可爱，你注定要生一个小…蠢货！

yingyinNormal.en: Coal and car pollutants often produce a permanent twilight in Shanghai, Beijing and other cities.
yingyinNormal.zh: 煤炭与汽车尾气污染物常制造出一种永久的暮色，笼罩于上海、北京和其他城市的上空。

yingyinNormal.en: Ted and his fellow California tomato growers produce close to 13 million tons of them every year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 泰德和其他的加州番茄种植者每年能收获将近一千三百万吨番茄。

yingyinNormal.en: Houston. Be advised we're going to deliberately breach the VAL to produce some reverse thrust. What?
yingyinNormal.zh: 休斯顿，我们要故意冲破阀门然后制造一个反向的助推力。你说什么？

yingyinNormal.en: These cows produce an energy resource that you don't have to dig, drill, ship, or pipe in. But a shovel does come in handy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些奶牛产生一种无需挖洞，钻孔，装船，输送的能源但要用到铁铲。

yingyinNormal.en: This mammoth markets brawled over one square kilometer. It provides 80% of all the agricultural produce consumed in Beijing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个大市场喧嚣鼎沸一平方多公里，它提供了北京消耗的农产品的八成。

yingyinNormal.en: I've known Mrs. Delfino for years. She pays for the grapes she eats in the produce section. She would never do anything bad.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我认识德尔非诺太太很多年了，她在品尝区吃两颗葡萄都要付钱，她绝不可能做什么坏事。

yingyinNormal.en: By the end of their journey, David's bees have travelled 8,500 miles and pollinated an estimated 5,000 acres of America's produce.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大卫的蜜蜂行经8500英里，给超过5000英亩的作物传授花粉。

yingyinNormal.en: And in the process produce a ripple effect that boosts wages for the middle class and spurs economic growth for the United States of America.
yingyinNormal.zh: 并带动连锁反应，不仅提高中产阶级的工资，也将刺激美国经济的增长。

yingyinNormal.en: David's story is disturbing to me. If the bees are in trouble, so are the farmers who depend on them and the consumers who want fresh produce.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大卫的故事对我影响很大，要是蜜蜂正在危险之中,那么那些依赖他们的农民，那些想吃新鲜水果的消费者。

yingyinNormal.en: Some produce is so popular, it has its own street. Guess where we are? Pumpkin street. This is onion Street. And this is Marrow Street. Unsurprisingly.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有些食品深受欢迎，成行成市了。猜猜我们在哪里？南瓜街。这是洋葱街。这个是西葫芦一条街。毫不奇怪。

examination_example.sentence: When people place their trust in an individual or an institution, their brains release oxytocin, a hormone that <highlight>produce</highlight> pleasurable feelings.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当人们信任一个人或一个机构时，他们的大脑会释放催产素，一种能让人产生愉悦感觉的激素。

examination_example.sentence: The Olympic bidders, by contrast, wanted to get more people doing sport and to <highlight>produce</highlight> more elite athletes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，奥运会申办者希望让更多的人从事体育运动，并培养出更多的精英运动员。

examination_example.sentence: Evidence that the LoveLife program <highlight>produces</highlight> lasting changes is limited and mixed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 证明LoveLife计划产生持久变化的证据是有限且混杂的。

sense_info_list.en: make or manufacture from components or raw materials

examination_example.sentence: The climate-friendly eggs are <highlight>produced</highlight> on specially designed farms.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这种对气候友好的鸡蛋是在专门设计的农场中生产的。

examination_example.sentence: The country <highlight>produces</highlight> only about 60 per cent of the food it eats, down from almost three-quarters in the late 1980s.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该国生产的食物只占其所吃食物的60%左右，比上世纪80年代末的近四分之三要低。

examination_example.sentence: "Mass-<highlight>produced</highlight> clothing, like fast food, fills a hunger and need, yet is non-durable and wasteful," Cline argues.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Cline认为“批量生产的服装，就像快餐一样，可以充饥并满足人们的需求，但却不耐用，也很浪费”。

sense_info_list.en: things that have been produced or grown, especially by farming

examination_example.sentence: It can be learned from the last paragraph that British people rely largely on imports for fresh <highlight>produce</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 从最后一段可以看出，英国人的新鲜农产品很大程度上依赖进口。

examination_example.sentence: Even with the most extreme measures we could meet only 30 per cent of our fresh <highlight>produce</highlight> needs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 即使采取最极端的措施，我们也只能满足30%的新鲜农产品需求。

sense_info_list.en: make something using creative or mental skills

examination_example.sentence: The Dutch giant Elsevier, which claims to publish 25% of the scientific papers <highlight>produced</highlight> in the world, made profits of more than £900m last year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 荷兰巨头爱思唯尔，声称其出版了全球25%的科学论文，去年获利超过9亿英镑。

examination_example.sentence: Even before the invention of the electric light bulb, the author <highlight>produced</highlight> a remarkable work of speculative fiction.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 甚至在电灯泡发明之前，该作者就创作了一部出色的推理小说。

sense_info_list.en: administer the financial and managerial aspects of a movie or broadcast or the staging of a play, opera, or others

examination_example.sentence_trans: 今天，戏剧的制作数量就足以使我们感到惊讶。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们的后代延续了这种可以自己制造叶绿素的能力，尽管直到它们吃掉足够多的藻类以获取这种必要的基因(它们还无法自己制造这种基因)，它们才能够从阳光中制造能量。

examination_example.sentence: PepsiCo's contribution was to <highlight>produce</highlight> healthier snacks that still tasted good.

examination_example.sentence: Green buildings like this aren't necessarily cost-efficient for the investor, but it does <highlight>produce</highlight> much less pollution than that caused by energy production through fossil fuels.

examination_example.sentence_trans: 但这种关注也引起了许多担忧。

examination_example.sentence: Tea is <highlight>produced</highlight> in many different areas in China.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 中国许多地区都产茶。

examination_example.sentence: The ink stick <highlight>produced</highlight> in Huizhou is of high quality.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 徽州生产的墨汁质量上乘。

examination_example.sentence: However, people there can <highlight>produce</highlight> vegetables without any difficulty now.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，那里的人们现在可以毫无困难地生产蔬菜了。

sense_info_list.en: create or form something as part of a physical, biological, or chemical process

examination_example.sentence: They flowered and even <highlight>produced</highlight> more seeds.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们开花，甚至结出更多的种子。

examination_example.sentence: Two or three times each year, the plants <highlight>produce</highlight> fruit.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些植物每年结两到三次果实。

examination_example.sentence: These flowers <highlight>produce</highlight> bananas.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些花产香蕉。

sense_info_list.en: make something using creative or mental skills

examination_example.sentence: Two famous skilled men and his son <highlight>produced</highlight> a kind of high-quality ink stick.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 两位著名的技术工人和他的儿子制作了一种高质量的墨棒。

examination_example.sentence: During a year, I had <highlight>produced</highlight> most of its recipes(食谱)and was ready for a bigger challenge(挑战).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在一年的时间里，我制作了大部分食谱，并准备好迎接更大的挑战。

examination_example.sentence: Some writers cannot <highlight>produce</highlight> a word unless they are poised behind a desk.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有些作家不伏案写作就写不出一个词来。

sense_info_list.en: things that have been made or grown, especially things connected with farming

examination_example.sentence: Each school built a garden, where children learned to grow their own fresh <highlight>produce</highlight>, like fruit and vegetables.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每所学校都建了一个花园，孩子们在那里学习种植自己的新鲜农产品，比如水果和蔬菜。

examination_example.sentence: Teaching children to grow their own <highlight>produce</highlight> is a great way to increase their preference for the <highlight>produce</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 教孩子种植自己的农产品是增加他们对农产品喜爱的好方法。

examination_example.sentence: The study found that vegetable intake if the children who grew their own <highlight>produce</highlight> increased greatly across the year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 研究发现，如果孩子种植自己的农产品，那么他们的年蔬菜摄入量会大大增加。

sense_info_list.en: administer the financial and managerial aspects of a movie or broadcast or the staging of a play, opera, or others

examination_example.sentence: How many documentaries has Rupert <highlight>produced</highlight> in the passage?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在这篇文章中，鲁珀特制作了多少纪录片？

examination_example.sentence: He has <highlight>produced</highlight> a documentary of the same name.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他制作了一部同名纪录片。

examination_example.sentence: Rupert has also <highlight>produced</highlight> the documentary Endangerous, with Rowan as host, about dangerous animals that are endangered.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 鲁珀特还制作了纪录片《濒危》，由罗文担任主持人，讲述的是濒临灭绝的危险动物。
